land by Romulus. So Alexander of Macedon gave the Uxii their lands, on the payment of tribute. So you often read that cities which surrendered, were not plundered. And we have said above, that not only persons, but the lands themselves of the cultivators, were often spared, with general approval, and according to the pious precept of the Canons, at least under tribute3 and that, under a like tribute, merchants have been accustomed to receive protection in war.
